Simeone went on to the pitch twice during extra time of his team's 4-1 loss in May, and confronted Varane, who had kicked a ball toward the Atletico dugout after the last goal.

During an often physical match, seven Atletico players and five from Real were booked.

For improper conduct by their players and for fans setting off fireworks, Atletico have been fined £16,500 and Real £14,250.

